(2922, 'Microsoft Windows 7', 'CVE-2012-0175', '94', '', 'Exec Code', '7/10/2012', '10/30/2018', '9.3', 'None', 'Remote', 'Medium', 'Not required', 'Complete', 'Complete', 'Complete', 'The Shell in Microsoft Windows XP SP2 and SP3, Windows Server 2003 SP2, Windows Vista SP2, Windows Server 2008 SP2, R2, and R2 SP1, and Windows 7 Gold and SP1 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code via a crafted name for a (1) file or (2) directory, aka \"Command Injection Vulnerability.\"'),
(2923, 'Microsoft Windows 7', 'CVE-2012-0174', '264', '', 'Bypass +Info', '5/8/2012', '10/12/2018', '1.7', 'None', 'Local', 'Low', 'Single system', 'Partial', 'None', 'None', 'Windows Firewall in tcpip.sys in Microsoft Windows Vista SP2, Windows Server 2008 SP2, R2, and R2 SP1, and Windows 7 Gold and SP1 does not properly enforce firewall rules for outbound broadcast packets, which allows remote attackers to obtain potentially sensitive information by observing broadcast traffic on a local network, aka \"Windows Firewall Bypass Vulnerability.\"'),
