(3188, 'Microsoft Windows 7', 'CVE-2010-1886', '264', '', 'Priv', '8/16/2010', '10/30/2018', '6.8', 'None', 'Local', 'Low', 'Single system', 'Complete', 'Complete', 'Complete', 'Microsoft Windows XP SP2 and SP3, Windows Server 2003 SP2, Windows Vista SP1 and SP2, Windows Server 2008 SP2 and R2, and Windows 7 allow local users to gain privileges by leveraging access to a process with NetworkService credentials, as demonstrated by TAPI Server, SQL Server, and IIS processes, and related to the Windows Service Isolation feature. NOTE: the vendor states that privilege escalation from NetworkService to LocalSystem does not cross a \"security boundary.\"'),
(3189, 'Microsoft Windows 7', 'CVE-2010-1883', '189', '', 'Exec Code Overflow', '10/13/2010', '10/30/2018', '9.3', 'Admin', 'Remote', 'Medium', 'Not required', 'Complete', 'Complete', 'Complete', 'Integer overflow in the Embedded OpenType (EOT) Font Engine in Microsoft Windows XP SP2 and SP3, Windows Server 2003 SP2, Windows Vista SP1 and SP2, Windows Server 2008 Gold, SP2, and R2, and Windows 7 allows remote attackers to execute arbitrary code via a crafted table in an embedded font, aka \"Embedded OpenType Font Integer Overflow Vulnerability.\"'),
